      "writtenOn": "2019-09-04T00:05:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d like Greg\u0027s take on this but my thought is that GrCaps subclasses should generally report what is possible internally and disables for color types used in public types (Image, Surface, Bitmap, Pixmap) should happen at a higher level. Maybe we need some cross-backend color type or imageinfo support checking that is further filtered by GrCaps for particular contexts/devices.\n\nI think disallowing renderability across the board might force us out of fast paths for tasks unrelated to clients making a SkSurface, e.g. rendering to gen mip maps, rescales, ... I\u0027m not making a hard claim about any of these in particular, just the general idea that we can render for internal reasons unrelated to client \"renderability\" and it might be useful to separate these conceptually.\n\nCC Greg",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 881,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 881,
        "endChar": 100
      },
      "revId": "79a6bbfb3625922a833ed45d29e8bbd64d0a34a4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "429cc22d_3fd6559d",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkCaps.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 21
      },
      "lineNbr": 881,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-04T01:01:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Having a higher level query for disabling SkSurface rendering for a given GrColorType seems like a good idea to me. However, the current system doesn\u0027t prohibit make GrColorTypes that we want to \"render\" to outside of SkSuface. Each backend still stores whether a given backend format is renderable in general (GL has canFormatBeFBOAttachment, Vk has a format renderable flag, etc.). So at least in you are inside some backend specific class they have queries to know what they can do with a format. If we want a function that is backend agnostic code it seems like we just need to add new virtuals and the backends just don\u0027t take the current ColorTypeInfo::kRenderable_Flag into concideration.",
      "parentUuid": "c6aca8cc_625efcf1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 881,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 881,
        "endChar": 100
      },
      "revId": "79a6bbfb3625922a833ed45d29e8bbd64d0a34a4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa76ad41_baa3ca73",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkCaps.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 21
      },
      "lineNbr": 881,
